Owners of Subaru cars insured by Kenya Orient Insurance will enjoy lower cost of repairs in case of accidents following a new deal between the insurer and Subaru Kenya.Under the partnership, Kenya Orient clients with Subaru cars will get discounts for spare parts, paint works and labour depending on scope of repairs, with up to 30 per cent discount on genuine parts.They will also not pay towing charges if the repairs are carried out at Subaru Kenya workshops. Kenya Orient Insurance managing director Muema Muindi said the partnership will reduce cost of accident repairs and delays for clients.